description: Try our easy to follow Crumbed Fish & Oven Baked Chips recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
keywords: Fish & chips,Pescatarian,Fish,High fibre,High protein,Tree nut free,Low sugar,Potato,Peanut free
name: Crumbed Fish & Oven Baked Chips Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 1 tbs capers in vinegar, drained, chopped

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 200Â°C. Line 2 large baking trays with baking paper.
Peel potatoes and cut into 1cm-thick long chips. Pat dry with paper towel. Toss with oil and season with salt. Spread on a tray in a single layer.
Place into oven on top shelf. Bake for 20 minutes, then move to the bottom shelf and bake for a further 10-15 minutes or until golden.
Meanwhile, combine breadcrumbs, parmesan, dill and capers in a bowl. Add butter and mix well to combine. Cut fish into pieces and place onto tray. Top with crumb mixture.
Bake for 8-10 minutes on top shelf of oven or until golden and fish is cooked. Garnish with chopped parsley and serve with chips, tartare sauce and lemon wedges.
